-- Portugal, Opposition Break Off 2011 Budget Talks, Diario Economico Reports
-- B y   A n a b e l a   R e i s
-- 2010-10-27T10:10:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/portugal-opposition-break-off-2011-budget-talks-diario-economico-reports.html
Portugal’s government and the Social
Democrats, the country’s biggest opposition party, broke off
talks on the 2011 budget proposal, Diario Economico reported
today, citing a person close to the negotiations.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anabela Reis at 
 areis1@bloomberg.net  